    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Maybe this should only be allowed under certain conditions?  Should a user be allowed to use a minimal config on mainnet, for example?  Also, as it stands right now, the validator just uses the config that we generate when running `beacon` or `init`.  Even so, the validator currently just uses whatever config we put in our rootDir when running `beacon` or `init`.  I feel like we have a few options:\r\n1) disable `--preset` for the validator command and have it continue to use the config generated in the `beacon` and/or `init` command\r\n2) allow `--preset` for the validator, but overwrite whatever config we may already have in the rootDir when `--preset` is passed to `validator`\r\n3) ???\r\n\r\n@dapplion thoughts?",
